Flatten veal scallops and ham strips with a meat tenderizer or rolling pin; cut veal and ham strips in half. On top of each piece of veal, place a strip of ham and one sage leaf Keep in place with a toothpick. Cook flat on the plancha for 4 to 5 minutes on each side. Season with salt and pepper then serve. Serving Suggestion: This goes well with spicy tomato sauce.